issue.title: Support for ALL Emoji
issue.body:
We face the same issue as https://github.com/ajaxorg/ace/issues/3404
When editing Emoji in ACE the cursor seems to be in the wrong location (too far right) making editing very hard (the issue happen per line).

There is an example with last version:
https://jsfiddle.net/9va6be3d/2/

If you go after the emoji, the gutter do not work correctly.

comment.body: We're facing a similar problem and are looking forward to a resolution. Thanks a lot

issue.title: Enable `ReadOnly` only for certain lines
issue.body:
### Describe the feature

It would be great if one could disable certain lines. Is this currently possible?

comment.body:
> what should we show for prefers reduced motion case, the same animation but slower?

The ideal would be to [completely eliminate motion](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/animation-from-interactions.html) when `prefers-reduced-motion` is enabled. Do you think a stationary version of this indicator would be clear to users that something is loading?

> As for screen reader, how much delay for autocompleters do we expect? I'd expect in typical case loading state to take much shorter than what it would take screenreader to announce start and end of loading state, so i'd say not announcing is better than announcing exactly the way it is displayed.

For some completers I could see it taking around 5-10 seconds to get results (e.g. AI based code suggestions), maybe we could read something to screen readers after e.g. 1 second, that should be slow enough to not be triggered by 'normal' completers but still offer an explanation for longer wait times?
